<span id="freeTextContainer12821176509972076008">Of all the Conroys I&apos;ve read so far, this is my least favorite. The book jacket describes Bull Meacham as someone you should hate but will wind up loving, anyway - but that was not my experience. I found very little loveable about<br/>&quot;The Great Santini&quot;. The thing that amazed me was how brave his family was on those occasions when they stood up to him. While I don&apos;t doubt he loved his family, and maybe was even proud of them in a way, he was domineering and controlling and sometimes downright cruel </span>
  <span id="freeText12821176509972076008" style="display:none">Of all the Conroys I've read so far, this is my least favorite. The book jacket describes Bull Meacham as someone you should hate but will wind up loving, anyway - but that was not my experience. I found very little loveable about<br />"The Great Santini". The thing that amazed me was how brave his family was on those occasions when they stood up to him. While I don't doubt he loved his family, and maybe was even proud of them in a way, he was domineering and controlling and sometimes downright cruel in his dealings with them. <br /></span>
