        <div class="reviewText stacked">
              <span id="reviewTextContainer45173337" class="readable"
              >
            
<span id="freeTextContainer1343393864097271501">This semi-fictional story is Pat Conroy&apos;s time growing up in Beaufort, South Carolina. I say &quot;semi-fictional&quot; because he transposed much of his life during that time (as a teenager) into the story&apos;s main character, Ben Meechum. It is a story of frustration, abuse, confusion, loyalty, and the hard road of growing up in a dysfunctional family. I enjoyed this book over the Prince of Tides, but not as much as The Lords of Discipline! </span>
  <span id="freeText1343393864097271501" style="display:none">This semi-fictional story is Pat Conroy's time growing up in Beaufort, South Carolina. I say "semi-fictional" because he transposed much of his life during that time (as a teenager) into the story's main character, Ben Meechum. It is a story of frustration, abuse, confusion, loyalty, and the hard road of growing up in a dysfunctional family. I enjoyed this book over the Prince of Tides, but not as much as The Lords of Discipline! </span>
